			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Albany</placeName> <date>September 8. 5611</date> A.M.</p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I was ordered to send you the<lb/> following for insertion in the next <sic>number</sic><lb/> of the Occident&#44; the bill for insertion fees to<lb/> be <sic>send</sic> to <persName>Simpson &#38; Beckel</persName> in <placeName>Albany</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">The Congregation Anshe Emeth</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">in <placeName>Albany N. Y.</placeName></p>
				<p>For consequence of the ill and unjust<lb/> treatment of a party of the Congregation Beth El<lb/> in <placeName>Albany</placeName> to the <persName>Rev. Dr. Wise</persName> 56 members<lb/> of this Congregation which were joined by 21<lb/> Israelites&#44; who had been no members of a<lb/> Synagogue previously to this time constituted<lb/> a new Congregation under the name of Anshe<lb/> Emeth &#40;men of truth&#41;.  This congregation is now<lb/> actively employed to build a Synagogue and a<lb/> school house&#44; which will be <sic>complesed</sic> as soon<lb/> as <date>Shebnoth</date> next.  At a regular meeting of<lb/> this congregation &#40;<date>September</date> <add>&#63;</add>&#41; the following officers were<lb/> elected&#58; <persName>Mr Joseph Spoiborg</persName> Parnass&#44; <persName>Mr. F<lb/> Schulz</persName> Cashier&#44; <persName>Mr. Maier Stern</persName>&#44; <persName>A. West&#45;<lb/>heimer</persName>&#44; and <persName>T. Klugman</persName> Trustees&#44; <persName>D. I. Levy</persName><lb/> Shamesh.  The <persName>Rev. Dr. Wise</persName>&#44; who resigned<lb/> his office in the Congregation Beth El&#44; was<lb/> then unanimously elected Rabbi of this<lb/> Congregation.  The whole chair went over to the<lb/> new Congregation&#44; consequently the divine service<lb/> now in a saloon furnished to that purpose&#44; is<lb/> held in the same solemn manner as formerly in<lb/> the Synagogue Beth El.  The school of <persName>Dr. Wise</persName><lb/> continues to exist with nearly the same <sic>numbre</sic><lb/> of pupils as before.  All difficulties between the</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>two Congregations were <sic>peacably</sic> settled and all<lb/> law suits dropped.  Brotherly feelings will soon<lb/> return.&#8221;</p>
				<p>I have to say something against your articles<lb/> though you did not yet come to the main point&#59;<lb/> but since I think to see you next week in<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; I do not write about it&#44;<lb/> I cannot answer <persName>Mr. Millers</persName> I have too<lb/> much work on hand.</p>
				<p>I am sorry to hear that you are unwell and<lb/> I hope to find you well next week.  I shall<lb/> not go away this time as fast or lately&#44; having<lb/> to talk a great deal with you.</p>
				<p>I feel now very well&#44; that I am relieved of all<lb/> domestic troubles&#44; and I hope now to settle with<lb/> all my literary opponents.  If I happen to<lb/> be <add>Hebrew</add> in <placeName>Phi</placeName> I should like to lecture in one<lb/> of the Synagogues in the german language&#59;<lb/> and if possible I would speak in the afternoon<lb/> on some subject in the english language.  I<lb/> think to be with you <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
				<p>I beg your pardon for my confused<lb/> writing&#44; I have too much work on hand</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Sincerely yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Dr Wise</persName></p>
			
